## v1.2.0 (2026-06-06)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus PR #1042 (closes #1040) — merged to main
**Verification:** verified-ci — fix merged to ProjectHephaestus main.

### What changed

- Added the **fail-fast-test pollution** dimension: adding new tests that intentionally trigger deterministic (non-transient) failures to a class whose code path goes through the module-level `_GH_BREAKER` singleton makes UNRELATED sibling tests fail with `GitHubUnavailableError: circuit breaker is open`. Each raised exception — even a fail-fast one — counts as one breaker failure; with `failure_threshold=5`, two new failure-triggering tests pushed the shared breaker OPEN and turned 5 later siblings red.
- Documented why `setup_method`'s `reset_all_circuit_breakers()` does NOT protect against this: the helper resets each registered breaker then `_registry.clear()`, ORPHANING the import-time-bound `_GH_BREAKER`. The fix is `module._GH_BREAKER.reset()` at the top of each new failure-triggering test (matches the file's existing `test_circuit_breaker_wraps_gh_call_impl` pattern).
- Added the PART-A motivating fix: `_NON_TRANSIENT_PATTERNS` in `hephaestus/automation/github_api.py` omitted HTTP 422 and GraphQL schema errors, so `_gh_call_impl` retried them 5× with `2**attempt` backoff (~31s wasted) even though they are deterministic. Added patterns `(?:^|\s)422(?:\s|$)|unprocessable entity`, `doesn't accept argument`, `is declared by .* but not used`.
- Added new `When to Use` triggers (fail-fast tests, sibling-test failures, registry-clear-vs-reset, extending a non-transient classifier, 422/GraphQL retry decision).
- Added `### Fail-Fast Test Pattern (v1.2.0)` workflow section.
- Added three new `Failed Attempts` rows (12–14): relying on `reset_all_circuit_breakers()` in `setup_method`; running only the new test in isolation; retrying 422/GraphQL-schema errors.
- Added `### v1.2.0 — Fail-Fast Test Reset + Non-Transient Retry Patterns` to Results & Parameters with the exact regex patterns and the one-line `module._GH_BREAKER.reset()` fix.
- Added ProjectHephaestus PR #1042 to `Verified On`.
- Bumped date to 2026-06-06, version to 1.2.0; expanded tags.

### Why

The v1.0.0/v1.1.0 versions covered "reset the held instance, not the registry" and "put the fixture in the right conftest scope." This amendment captures a third, distinct failure mode on the SAME `_GH_BREAKER` singleton: a class whose `setup_method` uses a registry-CLEARING reset helper (which orphans the bound singleton) silently accumulates breaker failures from any new failure-triggering tests, with the symptom appearing only when the whole class runs in file order. Same search surface ("my new fail-fast/error test broke sibling tests via the shared circuit breaker"), so it belongs in this skill rather than a duplicate.

